Export a Report to Run in the Background

To set up a report to run in the background, you have to export it in a special way.

Required Editions and User Permissions:
Available in: Salesforce Classic
Available in: All editions except Database.com

User Permissions Needed:
Background Report Export
View All Data
Modify All Data

Create a report in the Report Wizard.
Click Export Details and choose Run Background Export from the drop-down button.
Select a file encoding setting and a file format in which to export the report.
Choose how to save the report parameters.
Click Start Background Export.

When your report has finished running, a link to the report details is emailed to you. You can download report results from the report exports list. If a background export of a report fails, an email notification is sent to you.
